<p align=3D"left"><b>Instructions</b></p>

<p align=3D"left">To calculate the area and wetted perimeter=20
of a channel cross section, begin at the top of the left bank=20
and number each surveyed point, starting at 1,=20
proceeding to the right bank.=20
Enter the number of vertices in the form below,=20
then enter each vertex's x and y values. After entering=20
the required data, click the Calculate button=20
to obtain the cross-sections's area and wetted perimeter.=20
As written, the calculator can process up to 10 vertices.</p>

<p align=3D"left">After clicking=20
the Calculate button, the coordinate values,=20
area and perimeter will displayed using the specified number of=20
decimal digits. The coordinate values=20
displayed are those used to calculate the=20
area and perimeter, so changing the=20
displayed decimal digits may change the x=20
and y coordinate values and may result=20
in the calculation of different values=20
for the polygon's area and perimeter.=20
For many practical problems of interest, results=20
calculated and displayed using 3 decimal digits are adequate.</p>

<p align=3D"left">Clicking the Reset button=20
will erase the form's content and set the number of=20
vertices and displayed decimal digits to 3.</p>

